pageContext.description: Leaf shaped spearhead, narrow shoulderless wings, and a long wide socket which forms the very large keeled midrib. 2 Rivet holes and hollow wings. Socket is broken off.
pageContext.patina: Very dark brown - metal shows through all over.
pageContext.surface: Granular, broken and cracked in places. Chiefly along the line where the socket joins the wings.
pageContext.associations: One of a find of 50 associated objects, consisting of: 43 Rings, 1 spearhead, 1 ferrule (for spearhead), 4 armlets or bangles, and 1 penannular bracelet.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,No. 246 Murray Collection
